reviews.review_text: Stellar Matrix You da man Charlie boy.  The only thing better than a perfect SBD is a perfectly SBD/AUD matrix.  And it's for an amazing show.  5 stars for the audio quality + the significance of this show.

The Peak of The Dead All the shows from 88 -90 until Brent passed on were on another level. I look at all the strange critiques of these shows like an alien from another planet observing human mental problems. It was the energy, the college kids surging to get to these shows. Like another late 60's vibe. Obviously the band fed of the energy and responded happily to the good times. When you reflect on the Dead era's you can see this moment clearly and how special of a time it was. When you bounce to different Era's it is like night and day the difference between time spans. I recall older Dead Heads droning about how the old days were better almost jealous of this surge of positive vibes. Yes little clubs are great but the energy is capsulized in the late 80's on another level. The only comparison would be when Pigpen was a driving force during the 60's which had a similar energy boost. When I see knit pickers giving shows like this a 3 star rating I recognize them reflecting their own negativity. They are scripted like this ("Bobby's mic was too hot and Phil's bass was too low and this set's China Doll wasn't as good as in Philly") depressed people that are detached from the positive energy. The late 80's surge shows were awesome!
